# Project Coding Rules

## Type Checking & Linting
- **Ruff**: Used for linting, import sorting (isort), and code formatting
- **Pyright**: Used for type checking only
- Configuration is in `pyproject.toml`

## Import Order (enforced by Ruff)
1. Standard library imports
2. Third-party imports (`alembic`, `fastapi`, `pydantic`, `sqlalchemy`, etc.)
3. First-party/local imports (`app.*`)

## Type Checking Comments
- Do NOT use mypy-style `# type: ignore` comments
- Use Pyright-style: `# pyright: ignore[errorCode]` when needed
- The `alembic/` directory is excluded from type checking in `pyproject.toml`

## Git Commits (Conventional Commits)
Always follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):
- Format: `type(scope): short description`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`, `perf`, `build`
- Subject ≤ 72 chars, imperative mood, no trailing period
- **Never** add `Co-Authored-By` trailers
- See `.kilo/rules/commit.md` for full guidelines

## GitLens Configuration
GitLens is configured to respect conventional commits. See `.kilo/rules/commit.md` for VS Code settings.

## Running Tools
```bash
# Lint and auto-fix
ruff check . --fix

# Check imports
ruff check . --select I

# Format code
ruff format .
```
